The paper addresses the problem of weakly supervised object localization, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves adapting a pre-trained network for multi-label classification and object detection, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also mentions using segmentation cues to refine object bounding boxes, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
